There is no improvement required. The training of the salesperson is great. My onboarding was done seamlessly.

The whole process was quite shocking for me , the account and NetBanking activation all online and within minutes compared to all the signing/documents required many years ago! He explained all the features really well and the best part was no unnecessary push for taking products like credit card etc.

Highly recommend Subrata for his great attitude and behaviour. Please convey the feedback.

text:
I am an existing IDFC First Bank Select Credit Card customer and I got an option on my IDFC First Bank app to open this zero balance savings account with auto pay option enabled for credit card repayment.

The opening of account was very quick and smooth, however, when I received the welcome kit, it only contained my Debit Card while the covering letter mentioned that it'll contain a debit card and cheque book. I initially was a little worried when I couldn't find my cheque book in the welcome kit.

Eventually, I applied for cheque book containing 10 cheques through the IDFC First Bank app also I had to upload my signature to do the same.

I'd request your concerned team to clearly mention what all actually come with the welcome kit along with a check list for future new customers of your bank. Thanks

India is lacking skilled labor. This is true. At IDFC bank as well. The person at Barakhamba Branch with surname JHA who opened my account on his mobile did a huge mistake. He selected Barabanki instead of Barakhamba and opened the account. And on pointing his mistake, i choosed to close the account right away. 

If such people can't do their job properly, why they are doing it then. It is the loss of bank only. I should have kept the account if it would have been Barakhamba branch. And now, my money is not with IDFC bank and even my referrals are not for IDFC bank now. 

I felt threatened while interactig with JHA that day because i pointed out his huge mistake. And he wanted me to leave the bank asap as i was sitting there and waiting to talk to some senior about it. 

Bank should hire people via strict vetting. As business may go coz of such experience.
